## 6. Onboarding Checklist

Once approved, the following must be completed before the AI tool enters production:

- [ ] DPA signed and filed
- [ ] Model training opt-out confirmed in writing
- [ ] Tool added to {{ business_name }}'s AI Tool Register
- [ ] Data classification confirmed for all data the tool will process
- [ ] Access controls configured (role-based, minimum necessary)
- [ ] Logging enabled for prompts, outputs, and user activity
- [ ] Staff training completed for authorised users
- [ ] Data retention schedule defined for AI interactions
- [ ] Incident response procedures updated to include the new tool
- [ ] Review date set (6 months for initial review, then annually)

---

## 7. Ongoing Review

All approved AI tools must be reviewed:

- **6 months** after initial deployment (first review)
- **Annually** thereafter
- **Immediately** when the vendor changes terms, data processing locations, or ownership

Review must reassess:
- Continued business need
- Data handling compliance
- Vendor security posture
- Contract terms (especially model training and sub-processors)
- User access (remove unused accounts)

---

## 8. Emergency / Rapid Procurement

For urgent business needs requiring AI tool adoption within 48 hours:

1. Obtain verbal approval from {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }}
2. Restrict to **Public / Internal** data only until full evaluation is complete
3. Complete the full evaluation within 30 days
4. If the tool fails evaluation, decommission and delete all data within 7 days

---

## 9. Prohibited Procurement

The following AI tools must **not** be procured regardless of business case:

- Tools that do not offer model training opt-out for customer data
- Tools with no data deletion capability
- Tools that process Restricted data outside Australia without APP 8 safeguards
- Tools from vendors that refuse to sign a DPA
- Tools that have no security certification and refuse third-party audit

